<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q9_v1" title="Q9_v1" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>La masa molar de un compuesto químico se calcula sumando las masas molares de todos los átomos que lo conforman.</p>
    <p>Considera ahora el compuesto denominado nitrato de sodio.</p>
    <p>El nitrato de sodio, de fórmula NaNO₃, está formado por 1 átomo de sodio (Na), 1 átomo de nitrógeno (N) y 3 átomos de oxígeno (O). Las masas molares atómicas son: sodio 23 g/mol, nitrógeno 14 g/mol y oxígeno 16 g/mol.</p>
    <p>¿Cuál de las siguientes expresiones permite calcular la masa molar del nitrato de sodio?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfenced>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfenced>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:mfenced>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>16</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfenced>
            <m:mtext>(g/mol)</m:mtext>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión multiplica la suma de átomos por la suma de masas molares: (1 + 1 + 3) · (23 + 14 + 16) = 5 · 53 = 265 g/mol. La masa molar correcta se obtiene sumando los aportes de cada tipo de átomo: 1 · 23 + 1 · 14 + 3 · 16 = 23 + 14 + 48 = 85 g/mol.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfenced>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>16</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfenced>
            <m:mtext>(g/mol)</m:mtext>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Esta expresión suma el aporte de cada átomo del compuesto: 1 · 23 + 1 · 14 + 3 · 16 = 23 + 14 + 48 = 85 g/mol. Coincide con 1 átomo de Na, 1 átomo de N y 3 átomos de O en NaNO₃.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfenced>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfenced>
            <m:mtext>(g/mol)</m:mtext>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión calcula 1 · 23 + 1 · 14 + 1 · 16 + 3 = 23 + 14 + 16 + 3 = 56 g/mol. El 3 corresponde a la cantidad de átomos de oxígeno y debe multiplicar a 16, no sumarse al final. El aporte del oxígeno es 3 · 16 = 48 g/mol.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mfenced>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>16</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mfenced>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:mn>3</m:mn>
            <m:mtext>(g/mol)</m:mtext>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión multiplica por 3 toda la suma de masas: (23 + 14 + 16) · 3 = 53 · 3 = 159 g/mol. Pero solo el oxígeno aparece 3 veces. Sodio y nitrógeno aparecen una vez cada uno, por eso se debe calcular 1 · 23 + 1 · 14 + 3 · 16 = 85 g/mol.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar los átomos del compuesto</strong></p>
            <p>La fórmula del nitrato de sodio es NaNO₃. Esto indica:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> átomo de Na, </m:mtext>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> átomo de N y </m:mtext>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> átomos de O</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Escribir la masa molar de cada elemento</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>Na</m:mi>
                  <m:mtext>: </m:mtext>
                  <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> g/mol</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>N</m:mi>
                  <m:mtext>: </m:mtext>
                  <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> g/mol</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>O</m:mi>
                  <m:mtext>: </m:mtext>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> g/mol</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Multiplicar cada masa molar por la cantidad de átomos</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>48</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Sumar los aportes</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>48</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>85</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>La masa molar del nitrato de sodio es 85 g/mol.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 5: Comparar con las opciones</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión que representa exactamente ese cálculo es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>23</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>14</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>